President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Patricia A. Hoffman was nominated for Assistant Secretary for Electricity Delivery and Energy Reliability at the Department of Energy. Mari Del Carmen Aponte was nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of El Salvador at the Department of State. Donald E. Booth was nominated for Ambassador to the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia at the Department of State. Larry Persily was nominated for Federal Coordinator for Alaska Natural Gas Transportation Projects. Each nominee brings extensive experience and expertise to their respective roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them to bring about positive change for the American people.